text: Jhangi is one of the 51 Union Councils of Abbottabad District in the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province of Pakistan. It is also known as Jhangi Syedan to the local people. It is to the north of Abbottabad city (the district capital). It includes the northwestern parts of the city, its suburbs, and outlying villages. Jhangi is at 34°12'0N 73°13'60E with a height of 1201 metres (3943 feet).Location of Jhangi To the south is the city of Abbottabad. ==Subdivisions== The Union Councils is administratively subdivided into the following areas: *Banda Amlok *Banda Batang *Banda Falzullah *Banda Khair Khan *Banda Lamba *Banda Noor Ahmed *Banda Qazi *Banda Sher Khan *Bandi Gasan *Dheri *Dobather *Jhangi *Phagwarhan Other villages are: *Banda Buraj *Banda Jalal Khan *Banda Laman *Boi Di Gali *Laman Mera ==References== Category:Union councils of Abbottabad District
